  "title": "Dilaji: A New Chickpea Variety for Hills Zone of Assam, India",
  "abstract": "Dilaji, a new chickpea cultivar, was selected from 20 advanced chickpea lines in field evaluation trials in Assam, India, from 1992-98. It is high-yielding and has high protein content.",
